se entities you have already obtained a Wikipedia page for, and what information is still missing.  \n3. **Formulate `next_thought`** as a short, concrete sentence that (a) states what you have learned so far, (b) names the remaining entity or piece of evidence you still need, and (c) explains which tool you will use next and why.  \n4. **Select `next_tool_name`** from the allowed set: `search_wikipedia`, `lookup_wikipedia`, or `finish`.  \n   - Use **`search_wikipedia`** when you need to discover the exact article title for an entity you have not yet identified.  \n   - Use **`lookup_wikipedia`** when you already know the exact title and need the article text (or a specific fact) from it.  \n   - Use **`finish`** *only* when you have retrieved the full text of all three required Wikipedia pages (or you are certain no more relevant pages exist).  \n5. **Provide `next_tool_args`** as a **single‑line JSON object** matching the tool’s schema, e.g. `{"query": "…"} ` or `{"title": "…"} `. Do not include any extra whitespace or comments.  \n6. **Avoid unnecessary calls:** once a title is known and its page has been looked up, do not search for it again. Do not retrieve pages that are not directly needed to confirm the three entities.  \n7. **When calling `finish`**, leave `next_tool_args` empty (`{}`); the subsequent extraction module will read the trajectory and output the final list of titles.\n\n**Output format (exactly as shown, one field per line):**\n\n```\n</reference>\n\n## Claim context\n\nThis claim is provided only so you can understand the benchmark setting the downstream agent will face. Do not specialize the new prompt to this particular claim.\n\nThe coach alongside  will.i.am and Pixie Lott on The Voice Kids (UK TV series), and Aleksi Sihvonen, are both vocalist.\n\n## Output instructions\n\n- Write ONLY the new prompt inside <prompt>...</prompt> tags.\n- The prompt must remain general-purpose and preserve the same task and tool interface.\n- Do NOT explain your changes or reasoning.\n- Do NOT include <think> tags, markdown fences, or extra XML.\n\n<prompt><|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\n<think>\n\n</think>\n\n', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.7, top_p=1, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=32, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None, extra_args=None), prompt_token_ids: None, prompt_embeds shape: None, lora_request: None.
